metadata.name: Indian Garden spider with it's distinctive X web
metadata.description: Argiope anasuja or the St Andrew's cross spiders for their habit of resting in the web with paired legs outstretched in the shape of an X, the cross of St. Andrew. They also make a large white zigzag X in the centre of its web.
metadata.tags: Wildlife, Spider, photograph, India, garden spider, Argiope, anasuja
